        <div class="usat-g-tips-option">
            <h2 class="usat-g-tips-headline">USA TODAY Network SecureDrop</h2>
            <p class="usat-g-tips-description">To use USA TODAY Network's SecureDrop:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Use a public wi-fi hotspot at a place you don't frequent.</li>
                <li>Be aware of video security cameras so your screen isn't captured.</li>
                <li>Consider using Tails (https://tails.boum.org) for a higher level of security.  Tails is specifically designed to not leave traces of your web activity and includes Tor Browser.</li>
                <li>Install Tor Browser if you're not using Tails. Tor Browser allows access to our SecureDrop system, which operates as a Tor "hidden service."  Tor Browser is available at https://www.torproject.org.</li>
                <li>Open Tor Browser and type the following into the address bar: <strong>https://usatodayw7vu5egc.onion</strong></li>
                <li>Confirm you're on the USA TODAY Network SecureDrop system. The security certificate in the green address bar will note Gannett Co., Inc., USA TODAY Network's parent company.</li> 
                <li>Follow the instructions to send us information. Users will be given a codename that can be used to log back in and check for responses from reporters.</li>
            </ol>
            <p>Detailed SecureDrop instructions can be found at https://docs.securedrop.org/en/latest/source.html</p>
            <p>Tips for staying secure online can be found at at https://freedom.press/training/</p>
        </div>
